Sensitivity Models

Arthur M. Albuquerque

December 27, 2021

Tocilizumab vs. Sarilumab

Here are the sensitivity analyses priors. Here, we used the results from REMAP-CAP to define the SDs for both “Optimistic for Sarilumab” and “Optimistic for Tocilizumab” priors:

\[ \begin{align*} y_i & \sim Normal(\theta_i, \sigma_i^2) \tag{Likelihood}\\ \theta_i & \sim Normal(\mu, \tau^2)\\ \mu &= \beta_0 + \beta_1 x_i\\ \\ \beta_0 & \sim \operatorname{Normal}(0, 0.75^2) \tag{Priors}\\ \tau & \sim \operatorname{Log-Normal}(-1.975, 0.67^2)\\ \beta_{1[Sarilumab]} & \sim \operatorname{Normal}(-0.049, 0.118^2)\\ \beta_{1[Tocilizumab]} & \sim \operatorname{Normal}(0.049, 0.118^2)\\ \end{align*} \]
